      <description>Women infected by Candida albicans will most likely find the skin folds in different parts of the body, including the portion beneath the breasts and the genital area, showing unsightly purplish patches and uncomfortably itching.
For those who develop a yeast infection, or candida, skin tends to be scaly, red &amp;#38; inflamed. That is among the [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/yeast-infection-relief-blog/Yeast_Infection_Relief_Blog-Watch_Out_for_Candida_Skin_Infection.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: 1.27cm;">Women infected by Candida albicans will most likely find the skin folds in different parts of the body, including the portion beneath the breasts and the genital area, showing unsightly purplish patches and uncomfortably itching.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: 1.27cm;">For those who develop a yeast infection, or <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-relief/intestinal-candida/" target="_blank">candida</a><strong>, skin</strong> tends to be scaly, red &amp; inflamed. That is among the first stage symptoms.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: 1.27cm;">Candidiasis generally occurs in moist skin parts or mucous membranes. Small wonder even babies get it. Keeping babies diaper area clean is therefore crucial. Wearing very tight, synthetic undergarments; poor hygienic habits; certain medical conditions necessitating medications, like diabetes are some of the things that leads to <strong>Candida skin</strong> infection.</p>
