Candida infections can easily be diagnosed when it occurs in the genitals or oral area, unlike intestinal Candida which shows symptoms that can be mistaken from other illnesses. Too much intake of [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/yeast-infection-relief-blog/Yeast_Infection_Relief_Blog-Intestinal_Candida__Important_Information.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><em>Candida albicans</em> is a type of yeast which is naturally found in the human body. It is usually harmless when well-regulated by the body.</p>
<p>Candida infections can easily be diagnosed when it occurs in the genitals or oral area, unlike <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/" target="_blank">intestinal Candida</a> which shows symptoms that can be mistaken from other illnesses. Too much intake of antibiotics, which eliminates good bacteria, can cause intestinal Candida.</p>
<p>Weak immune system due to some disorders and/or stress can also induce the overgrowth of the bacteria. To avoid developing <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeastinfectionomore" target="_blank">yeast infection</a>, we should maintain a good diet and avoid too much sugar and processed foods.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
