      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify"><a title="sle" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/35194389@N03/3708944103/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0px;" title="female yeast infection " src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3450/3708944103_d011c4290d_m.jpg" border="0" alt="sle" /></a><small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="em iIie" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/35194389@N03/3708944103/" target="_blank">em iIie</a> </small>The <strong><a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-causes/how-women-get-a-yeast-infection/" target="_blank">female yeast infection </a></strong>is probably the most common problem of women. Yeast in general is not bad, considering it is found in various parts of your body  which is normal.</p>
