      <description>Candida is considered a normal flora or good bacteria that are microscopically seen throughout the body. Candida is the most common source of yeast infections that affect people.
It is harmless most of the time but if the body&amp;#8217;s resistance is weak and the immune system&amp;#8217;s shield lowers down, and then there is a big chance [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/yeast-infection-relief-blog/Yeast_Infection_Relief_Blog-Your_Guide_to_Candida_Rash.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">Candida is considered a normal flora or good bacteria that are microscopically seen throughout the body. <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-relief/candida-diet-recipes/" target="_blank">Candida</a> is the most common source of yeast infections that affect people.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">It is harmless most of the time but if the body&#8217;s resistance is weak and the immune system&#8217;s shield lowers down, and then there is a big chance this fungus will grow and multiply. As they say, too much of any thing is a bad thing.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">It is important, however to undergo tests to determine what type of Candida rash you may have; for every kind, there is a different approach to treatment.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify"><strong>Candida rash</strong> are normally seen in babies who constantly wear diapers. Symptoms include itching and burning sensation. It can be treated with ketoconazole, Nystatin and the like that are available over the counter. Also inspect other <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeastinfectionomore" target="_blank">yeast infections</a> such as oral thrush and the like.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">It is also best to manage and control your diet and personal hygiene that will help lessen your chances of having it or, if you do have it, at least lessen the symptoms discomfort.</p>
