      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">The symptoms and <strong>signs of a yeast infection</strong> include a thick, cottage cheese-like vaginal discharge, it can either give off an odor that will remind you of starch or sometimes its odorless, and the color of the discharge ranges from white to yellowish color.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">But not every woman experience discharge, generally it will leave your vagina itching all over. There may also be a sensation of burning and you will notice the vagina is vulva is swollen and inflamed.</p>
