      <description>Systemic Candida, an overgrowth of a type of fungus or yeast which proliferates in the vagina is moist and slightly acidic pH environment, is the culprit behind an estimated 95 percent of vaginal yeast infections.
This condition may proliferate if not effectively controlled, resulting to chronic vaginal yeast infections, not to mention mental distress and an [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/yeast-infection-relief-blog/Yeast_Infection_Relief_Blog-How_to_Control_Systemic_Candida.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="margin-bottom: 0.42cm; text-indent: 1.27cm;"><strong>Systemic Candida</strong>, an overgrowth of a type of fungus or yeast which proliferates in the vagina is moist and slightly acidic pH environment, is the culprit behind an estimated 95 percent of vaginal <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeastinfectionomore" target="_blank">yeast infections</a>.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0.42cm; text-indent: 1.27cm;">This condition may proliferate if not effectively controlled, resulting to chronic vaginal yeast infections, not to mention mental distress and an overall unhealthy feeling.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0.42cm; text-indent: 1.27cm;">It is highly recommended to get tested for <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Systemic Candida</strong> </a>if you are constantly feeling constipated or if you experience oral thrush or bouts with diarrhea, flatulence and itchiness of the rectum.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0.42cm; text-indent: 1.27cm;">To prevent your condition from recurring, know the factors upsetting the balance between good and bad bacteria in the digestive tract and vagina, like intake of antibiotics or contraceptives. Taking mutivitamins, good hygiene, getting sufficient sleep and eating a half cup of live culture yogurt daily also help support normal intestinal flora.</p>
