      <description>The symptoms of yeast infection can be uncomfortable. But more than causing extreme itchiness that can make anybody irritable, it can also be very dangerous when not treated quickly. When left untreated, the yeast will attach to the walls of the intestines and will create tiny holes.
These tiny perforations will allow toxins to enter your [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/yeast-infection-relief-blog/Yeast_Infection_Relief_Blog-Yeast_Infection_in_Blood.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The symptoms of <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-relief/yeast-infection-causes/" target="_blank">yeast infection </a>can be uncomfortable. But more than causing extreme itchiness that can make anybody irritable, it can also be very dangerous when not treated quickly. When left untreated, the yeast will attach to the walls of the intestines and will create tiny holes.</p>
<p>These tiny perforations will allow toxins to enter your bloodstream and will be circulated in the body in no time. When this happens, a person may experience heartburn, constipation, chronic diarrhea and may feel bloated. When yeast infection reaches your bloodstream, it now called <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-relief/how-to-control-systemic-candida/" target="_blank">systemic candida </a>disease.</p>
<p>When it is not given proper medical attention immediately, it can affect overall health condition and may give complications to the internal organs</p>
