      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Over-the-counter medicines are readily available to relieve treat <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/" target="_blank">vaginal infection</a> caused by yeast. Antifungal creams are applied topically in and around the affected area.</p>
<p>There are also powder and spray available to help relieve the itchiness and rashes. Others prefer taking antifungal medication orally, but it is not usually recommended by doctors because it has some side effects such as nausea, headache and abdominal pain. It is not recommended to be taken by pregnant women.</p>
<p>There are also suppositories or vaginal tablets, which are more preferred by doctors to treat <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-relief/your-guide-to-yeast-infection-relief/" target="_blank">yeast infection</a>. In cases of mixed infections, combination of treatments will be required.</p>
