      <description><![CDATA[Systemic yeast infection is the result of the rapid abnormal multiplication of Candida albicans or tropicalis fungi strain from the intestines. Its symptoms may be similar to that of diabetes. This type of yeast infection can be fatal because it compromises the bodys entire system.

 photo credit: Argonne National Laboratory It can start from one [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify"><strong>Systemic yeast infection</strong> is the result of the rapid abnormal multiplication of <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-relief/intestinal-candida/" target="_blank">Candida albicans</a> or tropicalis fungi strain from the intestines. Its symptoms may be similar to that of diabetes. This type of <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeastinfectionomore" target="_blank">yeast infection </a>can be fatal because it compromises the bodys entire system.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify"><a title="Jamie Stalker" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/35734278@N05/3702353406/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 10px;" title="Systemic Yeast Infection" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2430/3702353406_beed61ed1a_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Jamie Stalker" width="240" height="159" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Argonne National Laboratory" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/35734278@N05/3702353406/" target="_blank">Argonne National Laboratory</a></small> It can start from one part of the body or one organ, which may eventually spread if the body is not able to fight off the increasing growth of this infection.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">If not treated fairly enough, you may get complications like arthritis, gout, over fatigue, increased cholesterol levels, Crohns disease, asthma, irritable bowel syndrome, allergies, acid reflux, eczema, arteriosclerosis, psoriasis, acne, depression, and a lot more.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">Many of the diseases causes are not known. It is better to aid any treatment with a balanced diet and food supplements to increase your immune system.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/all-about-systemic-yeast-infection.html/feed</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
