      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify"><a title="Yeast infection relief" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/26122068@N02/3501168604/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 10px;" title="Yeast Infection Test" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3378/3501168604_8e4a9b7f5a_m.jpg" border="0" alt="yeast infection relief" width="240" height="180" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="BitchBuzz" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/26122068@N02/3501168604/" target="_blank">BitchBuzz</a></small>If you think you have a yeast infection, it is better if you do a <strong>yeast infection test</strong> first before taking any over the counter drug.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">Do not self-medicate as this may give rise to unnecessary complications or expenses. Contact your doctor and get a <strong>yeast infection test</strong> to rule out any other ailment. Your doctor will most probably give you a pelvic examination. This will examine your state and any vaginal discharge.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">He or she will also see if you have any irritation, swelling or any abnormality in and surrounding your vagina. Your doctor will then get a sample of your vaginal discharge and will be sent to the laboratory for further evaluation. If test results claim a yeast infection, the culprit would be the <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-relief/candida-diet-recipes/">Candida</a> strain.</p>
