      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Yeast infection relief" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24439436@N08/3700059481/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 10px;" title="Candida Diet Recipes" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2669/3700059481_14d777aff4_m.jpg" border="0" alt="yeast infection relief" width="240" height="160" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="zlakfoto" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/24439436@N08/3700059481/" target="_blank">zlakfoto</a></small> Candida diet recipes are very simple and have only a few ingredients. First, eating should be at least 3 times a day but with little or no snacks, especially sweets. If you need to eat in between meals, you should go for veggies or nuts.</p>
<p>Typical Candida diet meals are composed of meat, veggies and small portion of complex carbohydrates. The largest portion of a meal should be meat. The servings of meat and vegetables should almost be equal. For meat options, you may have ground buffalo, turkey or beef. It is also good to go for beef or chicken patties.</p>
<p>In chicken, be sure to choose the breast or the thigh part. Steaming is the best and recommended way to prepare your vegetables to retain the essential nutrients.</p>
