      <description><![CDATA[When the natural balance between the bad and the good bacteria is disrupted, an infection may occur. Yeasts can cause vaginal infection or oral thrush.
The superficial symptoms, such as itchiness and rashes can easily disappear with medication but some infection can be very invasive and enter the bloodstream. The main goal is to stop the [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>When the natural balance between the bad and the good bacteria is disrupted, an infection may occur. Yeasts can cause <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-relief/vaginal-yeast-infection-symptoms/" target="_blank">vaginal infection </a>or oral thrush.</p>
<p>The superficial symptoms, such as itchiness and rashes can easily disappear with medication but some infection can be very invasive and enter the bloodstream. The main goal is to stop the growth of <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-relief/candida-albicans-causes/" target="_blank">Candida </a>in the system. To do this, you should watch your diet and avoid simple sugars and high glycemic foods.</p>
<p>Refined carbohydrates should also be eliminated to starve the bacteria. Drinking plenty of water and adding probiotics such as <em>Lactobacillus acidophilus</em>will also prevent recurring infection</p>
