      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify"><a title="A cultured afternoon" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/53326337@N00/3435661897/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 10px;" title="Male Yeast Infection" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3662/3435661897_39bb5da16b_m.jpg" border="0" alt="yeast infection relief" width="160" height="240" /></a><br />
<small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="quinn.anya" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/53326337@N00/3435661897/" target="_blank">quinn.anya</a></small> Yeast infection in males are commonly the effects of prolonged use of antibiotics. Here are things you should know about home remedy <strong>male yeast infection treatment</strong>: Limit your food intake of dairy produce that usually have high contents of yeast.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">Clean your colon to make the acidity of your system become neutral. Yeast thrives on acid. Apply coconut oil that is cold or extra virgin coconut oil which is said to help fight off the yeast. It is also imortant to understand the <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeast-infection-relief/yeast-infection-causes/" target="_blank">causes of yeast infection</a>.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">Or try tea tree oil or cinnamon oil. Eat garlic. It is considered a natural anti-fungal therapy and is also antibacterial. Eat yogurt. To help relieve you of itching, try to have a sitz bath.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" align="justify">You may try over the counter medication like Monistat if you are in doubt of home remedies. It is still best to consult your trusted physician to help diagnose the real problem in a <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/yeastinfectionomore" target="_blank">yeast infection</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
