The most common symptom of vaginal yeast infection is [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Yeast infection relief" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/9399948@N05/3709296673/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 10px;" title="Vaginal Yeast Infection Symptoms" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3436/3709296673_2b5ecd6365_m.jpg" border="0" alt="yeast infection relief" width="240" height="180" /></a><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="frerieke" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/9399948@N05/3709296673/" target="_blank">frerieke</a>The fungus, <em>Candida albicans,</em> can cause infections to human. This can occur in different parts of the body like the intestines, penis and vagina.</p>
<p>Around 75% of women experience vaginal yeast infection during their lifetime. This kind of infection irritates that vagina and the vulva.</p>
<p>The most common symptom of vaginal yeast infection is the extreme itchiness inside and around the vagina. A woman can also experience burning sensation, swelling and redness of the vagina and the vulva.</p>
<p>Also, she may also find it painful while urinating and having sexual intercourse. There can also be a white discharge which looks like a cottage cheese.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
