The main sign of a baby with thrush is the appearance of white patches on the inside of the baby&#8217;s cheeks, it can also be on the tongue, [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><em>Candida albicans</em> causes vaginal infection and diaper rash. It can also affect young children and even newborns. When the <a href="http://www.yeastinfectionreliefblog.com" target="_self">yeast</a> affects a child&#8217;s mouth, it is called thrush.</p>
<p>The main sign of a baby with thrush is the appearance of white patches on the inside of the baby&#8217;s cheeks, it can also be on the tongue, on the roof the mouth, and sometimes it can spread to the lips and gums. These white patches cannot be wiped away easily, unlike the residue of formula milk on the tongue.</p>
<p>If someone would try to wipe it away, it will leave an ulcer and may bleed. Please be careful in this case as infection could follow.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
